\begin_body

\begin_layout Standard
Searching for moves
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Take 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 to be some sliding block puzzle that contains 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 rows and 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 columns.
 There are 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 blocks in this puzzle and each block in 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 has 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 different dimensions.
 The goal configuration can be described by the locations of 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 blocks that correspond to some subset of the blocks in 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

.
 A set of moves can be constructed s.t.
 each move describes the translation of a single block 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{0}\in b$
\end_inset

 by either a single row (
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq m_{0}\leq m$
\end_inset

) or a single column (
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq n_{0}\leq n$
\end_inset

).
 The first move from 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 to some new configuration 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{0}$
\end_inset

 can be described by
\series bold
 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{0}$
\end_inset


\series default
, the second move away from 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 can be described by 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}$
\end_inset

 and the procession from 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 to configuration 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{i}$
\end_inset

 can be described by a set of moves 
\begin_inset Formula $X=\{x_{0},x_{1},\ldots,x_{i}\}$
\end_inset

.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $f(B_{0},x)=B_{1}$
\end_inset

 accepts an initial configuration and some move 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and outputs a new configuration after that move has been completed.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The goal is to go from configuration 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 to configuration 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 that contains all blocks 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 in the correct position.
 
\end_layout

